Male (
holotype
). Body slender, flattened, subparallel, glabrous. Body strawy yellow, labrum, maxillar palpi and apices of mandibles darkened, head behind frontal tubercles brownish, scutellum and extreme sutural margins darkened, last two tarsomeres of all legs infuscated, base of first metatarsomere black. Antennomeres I–III yellow, antennomeres IV–V gradually darkened, antennomeres VI–XI black.

Ventral surface semiopaque, finely punctate and covered with pale setae. Anterior coxal cavities open posteriorly. Last ventrite with two incisions (
Fig. 23
).

Aedeagus slender, parallel, slightly extended subapically, with apex widely rounded (
Fig. 19
).

Female. Sexual dimorphism weakly developed. Last ventrite regularly rounded, without incisions. Spermatheca with globular nodulus, cornu C-shaped with prolonged apex (
Fig. 24
). Sternite VIII elongated, tignum very long, apically slightly dilated and bent (
Fig. 20
). Vaginal palpi with several long setae apically, basally forming long thin projection bifurcated posteriorly (
Fig. 21
). Ventral bursa sclerites sharp with two teeth at inner side (
Fig. 22
).
